How to run unit test suite
--------------------------
1. using PyCharm 2.6.3 (Windows)
2. using (Python) Command Prompt


1. Run unit test suite using PyCharm 2.6.3 (Windows)
----------------------------------------------------
- open "Run/Debug Configuration" window
- click plus icon "Add new Configuration"
- click on Python's test
- select Unittests
- give it (any) name (i.e. "Py UnitTests")
- under "Unittests" section select Script option
- open file picker and navigate to the .py file that extends unittest2.TestSuite class ("C:\...\app\tests\TestSuite.py")
- Ensure "Inspect only subclasses of unittest.TestCase" is selected
- click OK to save configuration and close the window
- [TODO: make generic] open BaseUnitTest.py file and set value of "datastore_file" property to reflect your local environment
- change active configuration and hit Play/Debug to run tests


